# VT Stats — Project Context

## Architecture

Static-site dashboard for Battlezone: Combat Commander match statistics. Three-part system:

1. **Python pipeline** (`scripts/process_stats.py`) reads raw `.binpb.gz` protobuf session files from `data/sessions/<username>/`, aggregates all statistics, and writes pre-computed JSON to `data/processed/`.
2. **Browser dashboard** (`index.html`, `js/theme.js`, `js/vtstats-fx.js`, `js/charts.js`, `js/charts-radar.js`, `js/positioning-charts.js`, `js/timeline-player.js`, `js/positioning-player.js`, `js/all-matches-aggregator.js`, `js/app.js`) loads the tiny pre-computed JSON files and renders interactive UI with tabbed navigation and glassmorphic theme layer. A client-side global filter layer derives player/team-scoped views from the loaded JSON without re-fetching. Statistical aggregation is the pipeline's responsibility with one **documented exception**: the All Matches view is built client-side by `js/all-matches-aggregator.js` from `data/processed/match_contributions.json` so it can scope to the picker-filtered subset of matches. The aggregator is pure summation — every per-match number it consumes was pre-computed by the pipeline.
3. **Raw Data Browser** (`raw.html`, `js/raw-browser.js`, `css/raw-browser.css`) is a standalone, isolated page for inspecting per-match data at every layer: raw binpb metadata + download, faithful client-side decode of the protobuf (vendored protobufjs-light + native `DecompressionStream`), and the processed JSON. Rendered as a virtualized JSON tree with domain-aware resolvers (Steam64 → nickname, ODF → prettified weapon/unit name via match-global `odf_map`). Loaded on demand per match from the main dashboard's "View raw" button on the match-info banner, or from the `docs.html` navbar.

## Key File Locations

- Proto schema (source of truth): `scripts/statsgate.proto`
- Pipeline: `scripts/process_stats.py`
- Radar renderer: `js/charts-radar.js` (Player Performance Radar — 8-axis spiderweb with single / compare / team / career modes; Survivability is a p95-clipped composite of damage-trade ratio and K/D, career mode adds Bayesian shrinkage toward the league mean; reuses `activeCharts` and `glassTooltipConfig` from `js/charts.js`)
- ODF weapon DB: `data/odf.min.json`
- Raw data: `data/sessions/<username>/*.binpb.gz` (gzip-compressed protobuf, organized by submitter)
- Processed output: `data/processed/*.json`
- Theme layer: `css/vtstats-theme.css` (glass surfaces, typography, animations, migrated inline styles)
- Effects engine: `js/vtstats-fx.js` (animated counters, entrance stagger, Chart.js shadow plugin)
- Replay player: `js/timeline-player.js` (Replay tab engine: animated timeline playback, transport controls, companion stats)
- Positioning renderers: `js/positioning-charts.js` (Positioning tab: Movement Leaderboard, combined + per-player heatmaps with shared viewport/intensity + legend, distance timeline, ring histogram)
- Positioning player: `js/positioning-player.js` (Positioning tab animated trail playback with transport controls, sub-second trail interpolation, teleport-segment gaps; exposes `window.VTPositionPlayer`)
- Match Highlights: `compute_highlights()` in `scripts/process_stats.py` (per-match award catalog — fixed slate of 12 always-on cards: The Bully, Grim Reaper, Bullet Sponge, Hustler, Sharpshooter, Gunner, Puppeteer, Frenemies, Roadrunner, Pod Goblin, Chris Kyle, Locksmith) + `renderHighlights()` + `HIGHLIGHT_COPY` in `js/app.js` + `.vt-highlights-card` / `.vt-highlight-tile` blocks in `css/vtstats-theme.css`. Section markup at `#section-highlights` in `index.html`, immediately above `#section-faction` inside `#tab-overview`. Match-global, always-unfiltered (renderer reads `currentData.highlights`, never the filtered `data` view). New top-level field added at `match.schema_version = 2`; pre-v2 matches simply have no block (UI hides the section). Cards self-omit when their data gates fail (positioning / pickups / T-key / snipe gates).
- Raw data browser: `raw.html` / `js/raw-browser.js` / `css/raw-browser.css` (standalone page: binpb metadata + decoded JSON + processed JSON; virtualized tree with Steam64/ODF resolvers; events-mode virtualized table with tick slider + filter chips + Replay cross-link; Reconcile view verifying tier-3 aggregates against tier-2 event sums; JSONPath subset search; proto schema tooltips)
- Vendored protobufjs + descriptor: `vendor/protobufjs/protobuf.min.js` (light build v7) and `vendor/protobufjs/statsgate.proto.json` (pre-compiled from `scripts/statsgate.proto` via `pbjs -t json`)
- Proto docs extractor + generated file: `scripts/extract_proto_docs.py` / `data/proto-docs.json` (parses inline proto comments for raw-browser field tooltips; invoked as part of `scripts/process_stats.py`)
- Map registry builder + generated assets: `scripts/build_map_registry.py` / `data/map-registry.json` / `data/maps/<mapFile>.{png,json}` (fetches map metadata + top-down image from iondriver's gamelistassets API, merges with `VSR_MAP_DATA` from `js/bz2api.js`; idempotent; invoked from `scripts/process_stats.py` *before* the manifest is written so `manifest[i].name` can be resolved from `registry[<key>].title` with iteratively-stripped `XYZ: ` prefixes — fallback is the `.bzn`-stripped filename)
- Vendored BZ2API library: `js/bz2api.js` (baked-in VSR map catalog + iondriver API client; consumed by `build_map_registry.py` and `js/app.js`)
- Schema-migration verify tool: `scripts/verify_proto_decode.mjs` (Node-based decode-and-compare against Python pipeline output; requires one-off `npm i --no-save protobufjs@7`)
- Sentinel damage audit + event-stream dump tools: `scripts/audit_sentinel_events.mjs` (histograms `amount > 1e6` events; must agree with the All Matches aggregator's `meta.total_sentinel_damage_dropped` output) and `scripts/dump_events_window.mjs` (general-purpose tick-range event dumper); both write to gitignored `_investigation/output/`
- Client-side All Matches aggregator: `js/all-matches-aggregator.js` (pure `VTAggregate.build(contributions, fileIds)` summation over `data/processed/match_contributions.json`; mirrors what `scripts/process_stats.py` `build_all_matches_aggregate()` used to produce, but folds in only the subset of file ids that pass the active picker facet filter). Loaded after `js/positioning-player.js` in `index.html`, before `js/app.js`.
- Picker filter contract: the match-picker modal (`#match-picker-modal`) carries facets — duration band, player count, submitter, full-roster Players (with Match-mode `any of these` / `all of these` and Role `any` / `Commander` / `Thug`). State is `pickerState` in `js/app.js`, persisted in sessionStorage under `vt.picker.filters.v2` (one-shot v1 migration on first read). The All Matches card subtitle, the All-Matches view's filter banner, and the trigger subtitles all update from `applyPickerFilters()`; when the user is on the All Matches view, a debounced `loadAllMatches()` rerun re-aggregates from cached contributions so the career table / radar / global meta reflect the new subset.
- Sentinel damage reference: `docs/DATA_DICTIONARY.md` §7 "Sentinel Damage Filter" (full evidence chain + decompile + struct layout for the `DAMAGE_TYPE_UNKNOWN` force-kill pathway; linked from rules + DEVELOPER_GUIDE). UnitDestroyed four-way classification + powerup economy reference: same dictionary §8.
- Team faction detection (ISDF / Hadean / Scion): `detect_team_factions()` in `scripts/process_stats.py` derives each team's faction from per-slot ODF first-letter votes (Algorithm A: starting-ship `PlayerState.odf` per slot; Algorithm B: event-stream votes from every team-attributed vehicle/structure/pilot ODF). Output at `match.team_factions = {"1": {"code", "name"} | null, "2": ...}`, sibling to `team_leaders`. Match-global, always-unfiltered. Bumped `match.schema_version` from 2 to 3. Faction badges render via `.vt-faction-badge[data-faction-code]` in `css/vtstats-theme.css` next to team-leader names in `renderFactionScoreboard()`. Full per-source vote table + edge cases: `docs/DATA_DICTIONARY.md` §9.
- Match winner inference: `compute_match_winner(kill_feed)` in `scripts/process_stats.py` derives `match.winner` from the cleaned kill feed via a toggle model on recycler/factory destructions. Outcomes are `clean_win` (one team fully dead, other untouched) / `contested` (both fully dead, tie-broken by fall order) / `unclear` (rebuild ambiguity, host quit, timeout, commander self-demo). Always emitted; `team` / `loser` are `null` for unclear. Renderer (`renderKillFeed()` in `js/app.js`) injects a `.vt-winner-badge[data-decided-by]` in the Kill Feed card header (with Bootstrap tooltip on contested/unclear), highlights the winning team's `.vt-faction-panel` with `.vt-faction-panel--winner`, and inserts an in-feed `.vt-killfeed-milestone` divider at `decided_at_tick`. **Filter-safe**: read winner from `currentData.match.winner`, never from the (filterable) `kills.feed`. Full toggle-model rationale + edge cases: `docs/DATA_DICTIONARY.md` §10.
- Vendored fonts: `vendor/fonts/` (Geist Sans + Geist Mono variable woff2)
- Technical spec: `DEVELOPER_GUIDE.md`
- Upstream collector source: `statsgate/` (reference copy of [statsgate](https://github.com/VTrider/statsgate))

## Data Flow

```
data/sessions/<username>/*.binpb.gz → process_stats.py → data/processed/*.json → browser → dashboard
                                           ↑
                                     data/odf.min.json (weapon name resolution)
```

## Session File Structure

Session files are organized by submitter username:
```
data/sessions/
├── VTrider/
│   ├── 2026-04-16-01-27-48.binpb.gz
│   └── ...
├── F9bomber/
│   └── ...
└── <other submitters>/
```

Filenames are timestamps (for uniqueness). Map names come from `header.map` inside the protobuf data. The submitter username (parent folder name) is captured in the pipeline output as metadata.

## Player Identity

Players are identified by `uint64` Steam64 IDs. The header provides:
- `s64_to_nick` — Steam64 → display name
- `teamnum_to_s64` — slot (1-10) → Steam64
- `s64_to_teamnum` — Steam64 → slot (reverse)

Faction is determined by slot convention: slots 1-5 = Team 1, slots 6-10 = Team 2.

## Dependencies

All dependencies are vendored locally in `vendor/`. No CDN usage. Bootstrap 5.3.2, Chart.js 4.4.7, Bootstrap Icons, Geist Sans 1.8.0, Geist Mono 1.8.0.
